org.jsonurl

Class Parser<V,C extends V,ABT,A extends C,JBT,J extends C,B extends V,M extends V,N extends V,S extends V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsonurl.Parser<V,C,ABT,A,JBT,J,B,M,N,S>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    JsonUrlParser, Parser.TransparentBuilder

    public class Parser<V,C extends V,ABT,A extends C,JBT,J extends C,B extends V,M extends V,N extends V,S extends V>
extends Object
    A JSON→URL text parser.

    An instance of this class may be used to parse JSON→URL text and instantiate JVM heap objects. The interface allows you to control the types and values of the Objects created.

    Normally this class isn't used by directly but rather it's subclassed with specific types and an instance of ValueFactory. If you don't need control over types you may use JsonUrlParser.

    Since:
    2019-09-01
    Author:
    jsonurl.org, David MacCormack
